<br>
However, over the last 24hours i have heard more and more talk about experience having been nerfed recently on the test server and i was concerned that this may actually be true.<br>
<br>
I just want to remind you all (the devs) that people will play EQ so long as it is fun and competitive. Remember luclin? Time sinks solved absolutely nothing. I had 14 real life friends that played EQ before the luclin expansion and now unfortunately only 5 are left. The idea behind having to spend 4hours in a group to gain one aa point was something that was not liked. Specially since almost every class needs atleast 100 aa points for the person to really be confortable with their character. Most of my real life friends had two characters they liked to play but because luclin destroyed their hopes of ever being comfortable with one character again (let alone two) they have quit one by one.<br>
<br>
What was it that had people stuck on everquest? If you ask me it was the ability to set out with a group of friends and discover norrath while doing quests and attaining new gear along the way. A lot has changed since EQ went live and most of those changes were for the best but some (mainly those introduced with SoL) were a killer for players like me. I dont consider myself a casual gamer but i dont have the time to spend 10+ hours on Everquest. I wish i did, but i dont.<br>
<br>
Everyone that plays everquest would like to have the best character. 500aa points, full Aten Ha Ra gear, etc. We all play for different reasons but bottom line we enjoy having a well equip'd character. Part of that feeling of a &quot;good&quot; character is aa points. I have many friends who have 250+ aa points, they are on day and night trying to get more experience. Unfortunately, i do not have 12-16 hours a day to dedicate to EQ like some i know and i feel very left behind with my 53aa points. Between school/work and raids i have very little time to actually grind out some experience and every day the gap grows bigger between me and those friends of mine.<br>
<br>
With this rate of experience i atually have a chance to catch up to the rest of my guildies in aa points and it has actually &quot;restarted the fire&quot; in me for EQ. I have found that im once again enjoying the game as i once was back before Kunark where i just dont want to ever log off.<br>
<br>
Here is my plea to you, please consider that those who have abused of your new exp bonus (level 65 already with 10-15aa points) are a MINORITY in everquest. And that minority will not quit just because they dont have to exp anymore in fact that will just give them more time to help others and do quests. Your hardcore players will always be around exp or not because they want to be the best and they want to stay ontop and in order to do so they will need to keep raiding. <p>Blaque Majik - 60 Sorcerer &lt;BR&gt;<br>
